    A TaskEvent describes a task event in a task's lifecycle. It consists of the following fields: - the jobId of this task's parent job - the taskIndex inside the job - the timestamp of when the event happened - the machineId where this task was scheduled on (could be null) - the eventType, which corresponds to an event transition code - the userName of the job submitter - the schedulingClass that roughly represents how latency-sensitive the task is - a priority where a larger value indicates higher importance - maxCPU which is the maximum amount of CPU the taskj is permitted to use - maxRAM which is the maximum amount of memory this task is allowed to use - maxDisk - a differentMachine field which, if true, indicates that the task must be scheduled on a different machine than any other currently task of the same job - a missingInfo field, indicating whether the record is a synthesized replacement
